<node TEXT=" OmegaLib Software" ID="Freemind_Link_19"   COLOR="#007FFF" STYLE="bubble" FOLDED="false"><edge COLOR="#007FFF" /><node TEXT="OmegaLib is a library that allows application programmers to access various interaction devices in a uniform and consistent manor" ID="Freemind_Link_20"   COLOR="#007FFF" STYLE="bubble" FOLDED="false"><edge COLOR="#007FFF" /><font BOLD="false" ITALIC="false" SIZE="14"/><node TEXT="This allows an application to easily include/exclude new interaction device" ID="Freemind_Link_21"   COLOR="#007FFF" STYLE="bubble" FOLDED="false"><edge COLOR="#007FFF" /><node TEXT="This flexibility also extends to a &quot;Type&quot; of devices" ID="Freemind_Link_22"   COLOR="#007FFF" STYLE="bubble" FOLDED="false"><edge COLOR="#007FFF" /></node>
<node TEXT="Such that within OmegaLib one type of head tracker (optitrack) can be swapped out with another (kinect)" ID="Freemind_Link_23"   COLOR="#007FFF" STYLE="bubble" FOLDED="false"><edge COLOR="#007FFF" /></node>
<node TEXT="This swap occurs with relative ease." ID="Freemind_Link_24"   COLOR="#007FFF" STYLE="bubble" FOLDED="false"><edge COLOR="#007FFF" /></node>
<node TEXT="More importantly the message passed by both are the same because they are part if the head tracker &quot;Type&quot;" ID="Freemind_Link_25"   COLOR="#007FFF" STYLE="bubble" FOLDED="false"><edge COLOR="#007FFF" /></node>
</node>
<node TEXT="Enables the application programmer to be unaware of the complexity involved in merging various devices together into one program." ID="Freemind_Link_26"   COLOR="#007FFF" STYLE="bubble" FOLDED="false"><edge COLOR="#007FFF" /><node TEXT="No knowledge of a specific device's API is need." ID="Freemind_Link_27"   COLOR="#007FFF" STYLE="bubble" FOLDED="false"><edge COLOR="#007FFF" /></node>
